<item>
            <title>[LU-4787] OOPS from null pointer dereference in mdc_unpack_acl</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4787</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A kernel oops is generated when body-&amp;gt;aclsize != 0 in mdc_unpack_acl, but posix_acl_from_xattr&lt;br/&gt;
returns a null pointer. The pointer is checked for error codes, but not for a null value.&lt;br/&gt;
The cause of the problem is most likely some data corruption on the MDT side, but the client should tolerate this by sending an error.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>ZFS based 2.5.1 MGS/MDS/OSS + 2.5.1 or in-kernel client</environment>
        <key id="23786">LU-4787</key>
